## Step 2: Modify `product-list.html` (Template)

Replace the content of `src/app/components/product-list/product-list.html` with the new control flow syntax and favorite UI.

```html
<div class="header">
  <h1>Online Store</h1>
  <span class="favorites-badge">❤️ {{ favoriteCount() }}</span>
</div>

<div class="view-toggle">
  <button
    [class.active]="!showFavoritesOnly()"
    (click)="showFavoritesOnly.set(false)">
    All Products
  </button>
  <button
    [class.active]="showFavoritesOnly()"
    (click)="showFavoritesOnly.set(true)">
    Favorites
  </button>
</div>

<div class="product-grid">
  @for (product of displayedProducts(); track product.id) {
    <div class="product-item">
      <app-product-card [product]="product"></app-product-card>
      <button
        class="favorite-btn"
        [class.is-favorite]="isFavorite(product.id)"
        (click)="toggleFavorite(product.id)">
        @if (isFavorite(product.id)) {
          ❤️
        } @else {
          🤍
        }
      </button>
    </div>
  } @empty {
    <p class="no-products">No products to display</p>
  }
</div>
```

**Explanation**:
- The header now shows a favorites counter with a heart.
- Two buttons toggle the view (All / Favorites). The `[class.active]` highlights the active button.
- The `@for` loop iterates over `displayedProducts()` and uses `track product.id` (required).
- Each product card is wrapped in a `div` with a favorite button below it (or beside it – you can adjust CSS).
- The button shows a filled heart if the product is favorited, otherwise an empty heart.
- `@empty` handles the case when `displayedProducts()` is empty (e.g., no favorites in favorites view).

